        {
            "_id": "FDGrNkxmckSR32ou",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Forge Breath",
            "sort": 1000000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The accursed forge-spurned breathes a cloud of stinging soot, ash, and glowing embers. This can affect either a @Template[type:cone|distance:30] or a @Template[type:burst|distance:20] centered on the accursed forge-spurned and persists for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<p>Creatures that move into or start their turn in the area take @Damage[12d6[fire]] damage (@Check[type:reflex|dc:36|basic:true] save).</p>\n<p>A creature that fails its save is also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Blinded] for 1 minute. Creatures within the cloud are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Concealed], though not from the accursed forge-spurned.</p>\n<p>The accursed forge-spurned can't use Forge Breath again until it has used Inflate Bellows.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "rarity": "common",
                    "value": [
